{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":719,"text":"Everyone needs a coach."},{"time":3612,"text":"It doesn't matter whether you're a basketball player,"},{"time":6713,"text":"a tennis player, a gymnast"},{"time":9991,"text":"or a bridge player."},{"time":12212,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14701,"text":"My bridge coach, Sharon Osberg,"},{"time":17160,"text":"says there are more pictures of the back of her head"},{"time":19415,"text":"than anyone else's in the world. (Laughter)"},{"time":22932,"text":"Sorry, Sharon. Here you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26594,"text":"We all need people who will give us feedback."},{"time":30185,"text":"That's how we improve."},{"time":32422,"text":"Unfortunately, there's one group of people"},{"time":35402,"text":"who get almost no systematic feedback"},{"time":38208,"text":"to help them do their jobs better,"},{"time":40393,"text":"and these people"},{"time":41792,"text":"have one of the most important jobs in the world."},{"time":44942,"text":"I'm talking about teachers."},{"time":47171,"text":"When Melinda and I learned"},{"time":49110,"text":"how little useful feedback most teachers get,"},{"time":52322,"text":"we were blown away."},{"time":54276,"text":"Until recently, over 98 percent of teachers"},{"time":58400,"text":"just got one word of feedback:"},{"time":61053,"text":"Satisfactory."},{"time":63773,"text":"If all my bridge coach ever told me"},{"time":66266,"text":"was that I was \"satisfactory,\""},{"time":68651,"text":"I would have no hope of ever getting better."},{"time":71428,"text":"How would I know who was the best?"},{"time":74726,"text":"How would I know what I was doing differently?"},{"time":78326,"text":"Today, districts are revamping"},{"time":80710,"text":"the way they evaluate teachers,"},{"time":82994,"text":"but we still give them almost no feedback"},{"time":86303,"text":"that actually helps them improve their practice."},{"time":89476,"text":"Our teachers deserve better."},{"time":92808,"text":"The system we have today isn't fair to them."},{"time":96036,"text":"It's not fair to students,"},{"time":97857,"text":"and it's putting America's global leadership at risk."},{"time":102887,"text":"So today I want to talk about how we can help all teachers"},{"time":106346,"text":"get the tools for improvement they want and deserve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110604,"text":"Let's start by asking who's doing well."},{"time":114470,"text":"Well, unfortunately there's no international ranking tables"},{"time":117938,"text":"for teacher feedback systems."},{"time":119864,"text":"So I looked at the countries"},{"time":121654,"text":"whose students perform well academically,"},{"time":124759,"text":"and looked at what they're doing"},{"time":127064,"text":"to help their teachers improve."},{"time":130103,"text":"Consider the rankings for reading proficiency."},{"time":133336,"text":"The U.S. isn't number one."},{"time":135826,"text":"We're not even in the top 10."},{"time":137881,"text":"We're tied for 15th with Iceland and Poland."},{"time":142819,"text":"Now, out of all the places"},{"time":145045,"text":"that do better than the U.S. in reading,"},{"time":147635,"text":"how many of them have a formal system"},{"time":150174,"text":"for helping teachers improve?"},{"time":153165,"text":"Eleven out of 14."},{"time":156000,"text":"The U.S. is tied for 15th in reading,"},{"time":158565,"text":"but we're 23rd in science and 31st in math."},{"time":163166,"text":"So there's really only one area where we're near the top,"},{"time":166250,"text":"and that's in failing to give our teachers"},{"time":168422,"text":"the help they need to develop their skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172043,"text":"Let's look at the best academic performer:"},{"time":175600,"text":"the province of Shanghai, China."},{"time":178765,"text":"Now, they rank number one across the board,"},{"time":182098,"text":"in reading, math and science,"},{"time":185017,"text":"and one of the keys to Shanghai's incredible success"},{"time":188388,"text":"is the way they help teachers keep improving."},{"time":192022,"text":"They made sure that younger teachers"},{"time":194351,"text":"get a chance to watch master teachers at work."},{"time":198018,"text":"They have weekly study groups,"},{"time":200292,"text":"where teachers get together and talk about what's working."},{"time":203126,"text":"They even require each teacher to observe"},{"time":206481,"text":"and give feedback to their colleagues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209619,"text":"You might ask, why is a system like this so important?"},{"time":213318,"text":"It's because there's so much variation"},{"time":216176,"text":"in the teaching profession."},{"time":218257,"text":"Some teachers are far more effective than others."},{"time":222414,"text":"In fact, there are teachers throughout the country"},{"time":225103,"text":"who are helping their students make extraordinary gains."},{"time":228656,"text":"If today's average teacher"},{"time":230899,"text":"could become as good as those teachers,"},{"time":233495,"text":"our students would be blowing away the rest of the world."},{"time":237671,"text":"So we need a system that helps all our teachers"},{"time":240578,"text":"be as good as the best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242590,"text":"What would that system look like?"},{"time":245187,"text":"Well, to find out, our foundation"},{"time":247212,"text":"has been working with 3,000 teachers"},{"time":249663,"text":"in districts across the country"},{"time":251847,"text":"on a project called Measures of Effective Teaching."},{"time":256066,"text":"We had observers watch videos"},{"time":258417,"text":"of teachers in the classroom"},{"time":260163,"text":"and rate how they did on a range of practices."},{"time":263751,"text":"For example, did they ask their students"},{"time":265589,"text":"challenging questions?"},{"time":267680,"text":"Did they find multiple ways to explain an idea?"},{"time":271997,"text":"We also had students fill out surveys with questions like,"},{"time":276497,"text":"\"Does your teacher know"},{"time":278210,"text":"when the class understands a lesson?\""},{"time":280767,"text":"\"Do you learn to correct your mistakes?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":283923,"text":"And what we found is very exciting."},{"time":286752,"text":"First, the teachers who did well on these observations"},{"time":290871,"text":"had far better student outcomes."},{"time":293322,"text":"So it tells us we're asking the right questions."},{"time":296580,"text":"And second, teachers in the program told us"},{"time":299393,"text":"that these videos and these surveys from the students"},{"time":302943,"text":"were very helpful diagnostic tools,"},{"time":305626,"text":"because they pointed to specific places"},{"time":308255,"text":"where they can improve."},{"time":310283,"text":"I want to show you what this video component of MET"},{"time":314326,"text":"looks like in action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316910,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":319857,"text":"(Video) Sarah Brown Wessling: Good morning everybody."},{"time":321538,"text":"Let's talk about what's going on today."},{"time":323706,"text":"To get started, we're doing a peer review day, okay?"},{"time":327055,"text":"A peer review day, and our goal by the end of class"},{"time":329510,"text":"is for you to be able to determine"},{"time":331393,"text":"whether or not you have moves to prove in your essays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334347,"text":"My name is Sarah Brown Wessling."},{"time":335816,"text":"I am a high school English teacher"},{"time":337501,"text":"at Johnston High School in Johnston, Iowa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339564,"text":"Turn to somebody next to you."},{"time":341311,"text":"Tell them what you think I mean when I talk about moves to prove. I've talk about --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344110,"text":"I think that there is a difference for teachers"},{"time":346771,"text":"between the abstract of how we see our practice"},{"time":350244,"text":"and then the concrete reality of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351887,"text":"Okay, so I would like you to please bring up your papers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355437,"text":"I think what video offers for us"},{"time":358080,"text":"is a certain degree of reality."},{"time":360394,"text":"You can't really dispute what you see on the video,"},{"time":363030,"text":"and there is a lot to be learned from that,"},{"time":365989,"text":"and there are a lot of ways that we can grow"},{"time":367918,"text":"as a profession when we actually get to see this."},{"time":370849,"text":"I just have a flip camera and a little tripod"},{"time":373842,"text":"and invested in this tiny little wide-angle lens."},{"time":377252,"text":"At the beginning of class, I just perch it"},{"time":379760,"text":"in the back of the classroom. It's not a perfect shot."},{"time":382185,"text":"It doesn't catch every little thing that's going on."},{"time":384923,"text":"But I can hear the sound. I can see a lot."},{"time":388203,"text":"And I'm able to learn a lot from it."},{"time":390252,"text":"So it really has been a simple"},{"time":393137,"text":"but powerful tool in my own reflection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395983,"text":"All right, let's take a look at the long one first, okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399032,"text":"Once I'm finished taping, then I put it in my computer,"},{"time":401800,"text":"and then I'll scan it and take a peek at it."},{"time":404436,"text":"If I don't write things down, I don't remember them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406548,"text":"So having the notes is a part of my thinking process,"},{"time":410203,"text":"and I discover what I'm seeing as I'm writing."},{"time":414290,"text":"I really have used it for my own personal growth"},{"time":416319,"text":"and my own personal reflection on teaching strategy"},{"time":419245,"text":"and methodology and classroom management,"},{"time":422514,"text":"and just all of those different facets of the classroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426020,"text":"I'm glad that we've actually done the process before"},{"time":428694,"text":"so we can kind of compare what works, what doesn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431219,"text":"I think that video exposes"},{"time":434544,"text":"so much of what's intrinsic to us as teachers"},{"time":438028,"text":"in ways that help us learn and help us understand,"},{"time":441185,"text":"and then help our broader communities understand"},{"time":443792,"text":"what this complex work is really all about."},{"time":447628,"text":"I think it is a way to exemplify and illustrate"},{"time":451760,"text":"things that we cannot convey in a lesson plan,"},{"time":454675,"text":"things you cannot convey in a standard,"},{"time":456828,"text":"things that you cannot even sometimes convey"},{"time":459057,"text":"in a book of pedagogy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461867,"text":"Alrighty, everybody, have a great weekend."},{"time":464233,"text":"I'll see you later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465469,"text":"[Every classroom could look like that]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467756,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473183,"text":"Bill Gates: One day, we'd like every classroom in America"},{"time":476155,"text":"to look something like that."},{"time":478839,"text":"But we still have more work to do."},{"time":481460,"text":"Diagnosing areas where a teacher needs to improve"},{"time":484180,"text":"is only half the battle."},{"time":486767,"text":"We also have to give them the tools they need"},{"time":489152,"text":"to act on the diagnosis."},{"time":491650,"text":"If you learn that you need to improve"},{"time":493565,"text":"the way you teach fractions,"},{"time":495306,"text":"you should be able to watch a video"},{"time":497814,"text":"of the best person in the world teaching fractions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501526,"text":"So building this complete teacher feedback"},{"time":504268,"text":"and improvement system won't be easy."},{"time":507378,"text":"For example, I know some teachers"},{"time":509388,"text":"aren't immediately comfortable with the idea"},{"time":511856,"text":"of a camera in the classroom."},{"time":514656,"text":"That's understandable, but our experience with MET"},{"time":517972,"text":"suggests that if teachers manage the process,"},{"time":521417,"text":"if they collect video in their own classrooms,"},{"time":523902,"text":"and they pick the lessons they want to submit,"},{"time":526878,"text":"a lot of them will be eager to participate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530639,"text":"Building this system will also require"},{"time":533592,"text":"a considerable investment."},{"time":536615,"text":"Our foundation estimates that it could cost"},{"time":539972,"text":"up to five billion dollars."},{"time":542127,"text":"Now that's a big number, but to put it in perspective,"},{"time":546481,"text":"it's less than two percent"},{"time":548474,"text":"of what we spend every year on teacher salaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552769,"text":"The impact for teachers would be phenomenal."},{"time":556081,"text":"We would finally have a way to give them feedback,"},{"time":560038,"text":"as well as the means to act on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562735,"text":"But this system would have"},{"time":563920,"text":"an even more important benefit for our country."},{"time":567710,"text":"It would put us on a path to making sure"},{"time":570883,"text":"all our students get a great education,"},{"time":574082,"text":"find a career that's fulfilling and rewarding,"},{"time":576773,"text":"and have a chance to live out their dreams."},{"time":580012,"text":"This wouldn't just make us a more successful country."},{"time":584366,"text":"It would also make us a more fair and just one, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589870,"text":"I'm excited about the opportunity"},{"time":592605,"text":"to give all our teachers the support they want and deserve."},{"time":597354,"text":"I hope you are too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599081,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600852,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}